[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1042},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F21\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F21\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F21\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F21\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics\u002F":1018,"related:\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F21\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics\u002F":1027},"\u002Freact\u002F20220921\u002F1348189923\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":999,"date":1000,"description":1001,"extension":1002,"lang":1003,"meta":1004,"navigation":85,"path":1005,"readingMinutes":1006,"seo":1007,"standalone":1008,"stem":1009,"tags":1010,"tldr":1015,"updated":1000,"url":1016,"__hash__":1017},"content\u002Fen\u002FReact\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics.md","React Basics: useState, the One Hook You Absolutely Have to Get (7)","1003096332",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":992},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,40,198,209,215,236,247,250,254,257,260,269,276,287,297,304,379,384,387,449,453,460,466,469,477,480,493,500,511,575,580,583,592,778,783,789,793,798,909,914,917,966,972,976,979,988],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"State is one of the most important things in React Hooks. How important? In short, the moment you need to change something that shows up on screen, you can't escape React state.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"vue-v-model","Vue v-model",[17,25,26,27,31,32,35,36,39],{},"Before I get into React state, I want to jog the memory of any Vue developers reading this. In Vue, when we need to bind data to a field on screen, we reach for ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"ref"," or ",[28,33,34],{},"reactive"," plus ",[28,37,38],{},"v-model"," to keep the data in sync.",[41,42,47],"pre",{"className":43,"code":44,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","const { createApp, ref } = Vue;\n\nconst app = createApp({\n  setup() {\n    const text = ref('Hello Ray.');\n    \n    return {\n      text,\n    }\n  }\n});\n\napp.mount('#app');\n","js","",[28,48,49,80,87,105,114,138,144,153,159,165,171,177,182],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,51,54,58,62,66,69,71,74,77],"span",{"class":52,"line":53},"line",1,[50,55,57],{"class":56},"sWyjQ","const",[50,59,61],{"class":60},"sMAXC"," { ",[50,63,65],{"class":64},"sCcAr","createApp",[50,67,68],{"class":60},", ",[50,70,30],{"class":64},[50,72,73],{"class":60}," } ",[50,75,76],{"class":56},"=",[50,78,79],{"class":60}," Vue;\n",[50,81,83],{"class":52,"line":82},2,[50,84,86],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":85},true,"\n",[50,88,90,92,95,98,102],{"class":52,"line":89},3,[50,91,57],{"class":56},[50,93,94],{"class":64}," app",[50,96,97],{"class":56}," =",[50,99,101],{"class":100},"sj_SG"," createApp",[50,103,104],{"class":60},"({\n",[50,106,108,111],{"class":52,"line":107},4,[50,109,110],{"class":100},"  setup",[50,112,113],{"class":60},"() {\n",[50,115,117,120,123,125,128,131,135],{"class":52,"line":116},5,[50,118,119],{"class":56},"    const",[50,121,122],{"class":64}," text",[50,124,97],{"class":56},[50,126,127],{"class":100}," ref",[50,129,130],{"class":60},"(",[50,132,134],{"class":133},"sTRMh","'Hello Ray.'",[50,136,137],{"class":60},");\n",[50,139,141],{"class":52,"line":140},6,[50,142,143],{"class":60},"    \n",[50,145,147,150],{"class":52,"line":146},7,[50,148,149],{"class":56},"    return",[50,151,152],{"class":60}," {\n",[50,154,156],{"class":52,"line":155},8,[50,157,158],{"class":60},"      text,\n",[50,160,162],{"class":52,"line":161},9,[50,163,164],{"class":60},"    }\n",[50,166,168],{"class":52,"line":167},10,[50,169,170],{"class":60},"  }\n",[50,172,174],{"class":52,"line":173},11,[50,175,176],{"class":60},"});\n",[50,178,180],{"class":52,"line":179},12,[50,181,86],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":85},[50,183,185,188,191,193,196],{"class":52,"line":184},13,[50,186,187],{"class":60},"app.",[50,189,190],{"class":100},"mount",[50,192,130],{"class":60},[50,194,195],{"class":133},"'#app'",[50,197,137],{"class":60},[199,200,208],"iframe",{"height":201,"style":202,"scrolling":203,"title":204,"src":205,"frameBorder":203,"loading":206,"allowTransparency":207,"allowFullScreen":207},300,"width: 100%;","no","(55)Vue Nested Components","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FQWmYRqy?default-tab=html%2Cresult","lazy","true","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FQWmYRqy\">\n  (55)Vue Nested Components\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,210,211,212,214],{},"With the ",[28,213,38],{}," directive you can update the data and trigger a re-render to refresh the screen, all in one go. That's what we call two-way binding. If you're curious about how that binding actually works under the hood, I've written about it before:",[216,217,218,229],"ul",{},[219,220,221,228],"li",{},[222,223,227],"a",{"href":224,"rel":225},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fvue\u002F20210607\u002F665675438\u002F",[226],"nofollow","A Gentle Intro to Vue 2 Two-Way Binding — Concept and Implementation"," (article in Mandarin)",[219,230,231,228],{},[222,232,235],{"href":233,"rel":234},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fvue\u002F20210627\u002F555169856\u002F",[226],"A Gentle Intro to Vue 3 Two-Way Binding — Concept and Implementation",[17,237,238,239,242,243,246],{},"One thing to note: the underlying implementation differs between Vue 2 and Vue 3 — Vue 2 uses ",[28,240,241],{},"Object.defineProperty",", while Vue 3 uses the ES6 ",[28,244,245],{},"Proxy",". So they're not the same thing.",[17,248,249],{},"So what about React? Is it similar? Let's look at how React deals with data.",[12,251,253],{"id":252},"react-state","React State",[17,255,256],{},"We've covered a lot of React stuff in the earlier chapters, and I touched on Vue's two-way binding too. But honestly, we haven't actually started on React Hooks yet — not a single hook so far.",[17,258,259],{},"So now it's time to introduce the first one: the State Hook.",[17,261,262,263,265,266,268],{},"\"State\" basically means the status of something — specifically, the status of your data. In that sense it's a lot like Vue's ",[28,264,30],{}," and ",[28,267,34],{},", because we pass in an initial value for the state to watch.",[17,270,271,272,275],{},"There's a small difference in React though. The State Hook is really just referring to the ",[28,273,274],{},"useState"," function. The basic syntax looks like this:",[41,277,281],{"className":278,"code":279,"language":280,"meta":46,"style":46},"language-jsx shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","const [myName, setMyName] = React.useState('Ray');\n","jsx",[28,282,283],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,284,285],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,286,279],{},[17,288,289,291,292,296],{},[28,290,274],{}," returns an array, and we usually pull out the two values with ",[293,294,295],"strong",{},"array destructuring",". The first one is the plain data used for rendering on screen, and the second one is how you tell React the data has changed, so it should re-render.",[17,298,299,300,303],{},"For example, say you've got a button on screen and clicking it should swap the content. If you don't use ",[28,301,302],{},"setMyName",", nothing happens:",[41,305,307],{"className":278,"code":306,"language":280,"meta":46,"style":46},"const App = () => {\n  let [myName, setMyName] = React.useState('Ray');\n \n  return (\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      { myName }\n      \u003Cbutton type=\"button\" onClick={ () => myName = 'QQ' }>Rename\u003C\u002Fbutton>\n    \u003C\u002Fdiv>\n  )\n}\n\nconst app = document.querySelector('#app');\nconst root = ReactDOM.createRoot(app);\nroot.render(\u003CApp \u002F>);\n",[28,308,309,314,319,324,329,334,339,344,349,354,359,363,368,373],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,310,311],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,312,313],{},"const App = () => {\n",[50,315,316],{"class":52,"line":82},[50,317,318],{},"  let [myName, setMyName] = React.useState('Ray');\n",[50,320,321],{"class":52,"line":89},[50,322,323],{}," \n",[50,325,326],{"class":52,"line":107},[50,327,328],{},"  return (\n",[50,330,331],{"class":52,"line":116},[50,332,333],{},"    \u003Cdiv>\n",[50,335,336],{"class":52,"line":140},[50,337,338],{},"      { myName }\n",[50,340,341],{"class":52,"line":146},[50,342,343],{},"      \u003Cbutton type=\"button\" onClick={ () => myName = 'QQ' }>Rename\u003C\u002Fbutton>\n",[50,345,346],{"class":52,"line":155},[50,347,348],{},"    \u003C\u002Fdiv>\n",[50,350,351],{"class":52,"line":161},[50,352,353],{},"  )\n",[50,355,356],{"class":52,"line":167},[50,357,358],{},"}\n",[50,360,361],{"class":52,"line":173},[50,362,86],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":85},[50,364,365],{"class":52,"line":179},[50,366,367],{},"const app = document.querySelector('#app');\n",[50,369,370],{"class":52,"line":184},[50,371,372],{},"const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(app);\n",[50,374,376],{"class":52,"line":375},14,[50,377,378],{},"root.render(\u003CApp \u002F>);\n",[199,380,383],{"height":201,"style":202,"scrolling":203,"title":381,"src":382,"frameBorder":203,"loading":206,"allowTransparency":207,"allowFullScreen":207},"(64) React State Hook","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FeYMxwpr?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FeYMxwpr\">\n  (64) React State Hook\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,385,386],{},"The reason is that if you want to change the value, you have to go through the second destructured variable — that's the correct way to do it. And one thing to watch out for: that second variable is a function.",[41,388,390],{"className":278,"code":389,"language":280,"meta":46,"style":46},"const App = () => {\n  let [myName, setMyName] = React.useState('Ray');\n \n  return (\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      { myName }\n      \u003Cbutton type=\"button\" onClick={ () => setMyName('QQ') }>Rename\u003C\u002Fbutton>\n    \u003C\u002Fdiv>\n  )\n}\n\nconst app = document.querySelector('#app');\nconst root = ReactDOM.createRoot(app);\nroot.render(\u003CApp \u002F>);\n",[28,391,392,396,400,404,408,412,416,421,425,429,433,437,441,445],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,393,394],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,395,313],{},[50,397,398],{"class":52,"line":82},[50,399,318],{},[50,401,402],{"class":52,"line":89},[50,403,323],{},[50,405,406],{"class":52,"line":107},[50,407,328],{},[50,409,410],{"class":52,"line":116},[50,411,333],{},[50,413,414],{"class":52,"line":140},[50,415,338],{},[50,417,418],{"class":52,"line":146},[50,419,420],{},"      \u003Cbutton type=\"button\" onClick={ () => setMyName('QQ') }>Rename\u003C\u002Fbutton>\n",[50,422,423],{"class":52,"line":155},[50,424,348],{},[50,426,427],{"class":52,"line":161},[50,428,353],{},[50,430,431],{"class":52,"line":167},[50,432,358],{},[50,434,435],{"class":52,"line":173},[50,436,86],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":85},[50,438,439],{"class":52,"line":179},[50,440,367],{},[50,442,443],{"class":52,"line":184},[50,444,372],{},[50,446,447],{"class":52,"line":375},[50,448,378],{},[199,450,452],{"height":201,"style":202,"scrolling":203,"title":381,"src":451,"frameBorder":203,"loading":206,"allowTransparency":207,"allowFullScreen":207},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FWNzPqrj?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FWNzPqrj\">\n  (64) React State Hook\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,454,455,456,459],{},"What this shows is that in React, you have to ",[293,457,458],{},"decide when to trigger the function yourself"," — that's the only way the screen re-renders.",[17,461,462,463,465],{},"The second value (",[28,464,302],{},") exists specifically to trigger that re-render, and this is a different situation from Vue. In Vue, changing the data updates the screen immediately. In React, you get to decide when the screen updates. This is exactly why people say React's data is one-way bound: we just bind the data to the screen, and even if the data updates, we can choose not to update the view. As long as you don't call that specific function, the screen won't change. Vue is the opposite — any time the data changes, the screen will update (unless you wrote something wrong or stepped on a landmine).",[17,467,468],{},"Before you start writing hooks, remember the React Hook rules I mentioned in earlier chapters:",[216,470,471,474],{},[219,472,473],{},"Only call them at the top level of a function",[219,475,476],{},"Only use them in Function Components",[17,478,479],{},"Because this is important!\nBecause this is important!\nBecause this is important!",[17,481,482,483,485,486,488,489,492],{},"Back to ",[28,484,274],{}," — so what does ",[28,487,274],{}," actually do? After we pass in a string, it returns an array that looks like ",[28,490,491],{},"Array [ \"Ray\", dispatchSetState() ]",".",[17,494,495],{},[496,497],"img",{"alt":498,"src":499},"useState return value in the console","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002Fithelp2022-react\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-08-21%2021.31.35.png",[17,501,502,503,506,507,510],{},"Like I said earlier, the first item from destructuring is a plain value — the value you passed in — and the second is a function. The ",[28,504,505],{},"dispatchSetState"," function is what triggers the re-render, so when ",[28,508,509],{},"myName","'s value updates, the screen updates with it.",[41,512,514],{"className":278,"code":513,"language":280,"meta":46,"style":46},"const App = () => {\n  const [myName, setMyName] = React.useState('Ray');\n  \n  return (\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      { myName }\n      \u003Cbutton type=\"button\" onClick={ () => setMyName('Mr. QQ') }>Change name\u003C\u002Fbutton>\n    \u003C\u002Fdiv>\n  )\n}\n\nconst app = document.querySelector('#app');\nconst root = ReactDOM.createRoot(app);\nroot.render(\u003CApp \u002F>);\n",[28,515,516,520,525,530,534,538,542,547,551,555,559,563,567,571],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,517,518],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,519,313],{},[50,521,522],{"class":52,"line":82},[50,523,524],{},"  const [myName, setMyName] = React.useState('Ray');\n",[50,526,527],{"class":52,"line":89},[50,528,529],{},"  \n",[50,531,532],{"class":52,"line":107},[50,533,328],{},[50,535,536],{"class":52,"line":116},[50,537,333],{},[50,539,540],{"class":52,"line":140},[50,541,338],{},[50,543,544],{"class":52,"line":146},[50,545,546],{},"      \u003Cbutton type=\"button\" onClick={ () => setMyName('Mr. QQ') }>Change name\u003C\u002Fbutton>\n",[50,548,549],{"class":52,"line":155},[50,550,348],{},[50,552,553],{"class":52,"line":161},[50,554,353],{},[50,556,557],{"class":52,"line":167},[50,558,358],{},[50,560,561],{"class":52,"line":173},[50,562,86],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":85},[50,564,565],{"class":52,"line":179},[50,566,367],{},[50,568,569],{"class":52,"line":184},[50,570,372],{},[50,572,573],{"class":52,"line":375},[50,574,378],{},[199,576,579],{"height":201,"style":202,"scrolling":203,"title":577,"src":578,"frameBorder":203,"loading":206,"allowTransparency":207,"allowFullScreen":207},"(65) React State Hook","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FyLKwBEM?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FyLKwBEM\">\n  (65) React State Hook\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,581,582],{},"When you click the \"Change name\" button, you'll see the string on screen re-render along with it.",[17,584,585,586,588,589,591],{},"But what if we didn't use ",[28,587,274],{},"? Could we still update it? Honestly, experimenting is the best way to learn, so go ahead and try declaring a plain variable without ",[28,590,274],{}," and changing its value directly:",[41,593,595],{"className":43,"code":594,"language":45,"meta":46,"style":46},"const App = () => {\n  let myName = 'Ray';\n  return (\n    \u003Cdiv>\n      { myName }\n      \u003Cbutton type=\"button\" onClick={ () => myName = 'Mr. QQ' }>Change name\u003C\u002Fbutton>\n    \u003C\u002Fdiv>\n  )\n}\n\nconst app = document.querySelector('#app');\nconst root = ReactDOM.createRoot(app);\nroot.render(\u003CApp \u002F>);\n",[28,596,597,614,630,638,650,659,702,711,715,719,723,743,761],{"__ignoreMap":46},[50,598,599,601,604,606,609,612],{"class":52,"line":53},[50,600,57],{"class":56},[50,602,603],{"class":100}," App",[50,605,97],{"class":56},[50,607,608],{"class":60}," () ",[50,610,611],{"class":56},"=>",[50,613,152],{"class":60},[50,615,616,619,622,624,627],{"class":52,"line":82},[50,617,618],{"class":56},"  let",[50,620,621],{"class":60}," myName ",[50,623,76],{"class":56},[50,625,626],{"class":133}," 'Ray'",[50,628,629],{"class":60},";\n",[50,631,632,635],{"class":52,"line":89},[50,633,634],{"class":56},"  return",[50,636,637],{"class":60}," (\n",[50,639,640,643,647],{"class":52,"line":107},[50,641,642],{"class":60},"    \u003C",[50,644,646],{"class":645},"sKpQp","div",[50,648,649],{"class":60},">\n",[50,651,652,655,657],{"class":52,"line":116},[50,653,654],{"class":56},"      {",[50,656,621],{"class":60},[50,658,358],{"class":56},[50,660,661,664,667,670,672,675,678,681,683,685,687,689,692,695,698,700],{"class":52,"line":140},[50,662,663],{"class":60},"      \u003C",[50,665,666],{"class":645},"button",[50,668,669],{"class":64}," type",[50,671,76],{"class":56},[50,673,674],{"class":133},"\"button\"",[50,676,677],{"class":64}," onClick",[50,679,680],{"class":56},"={",[50,682,608],{"class":60},[50,684,611],{"class":56},[50,686,621],{"class":60},[50,688,76],{"class":56},[50,690,691],{"class":133}," 'Mr. QQ'",[50,693,694],{"class":56}," }",[50,696,697],{"class":60},">Change name\u003C\u002F",[50,699,666],{"class":645},[50,701,649],{"class":60},[50,703,704,707,709],{"class":52,"line":146},[50,705,706],{"class":60},"    \u003C\u002F",[50,708,646],{"class":645},[50,710,649],{"class":60},[50,712,713],{"class":52,"line":155},[50,714,353],{"class":60},[50,716,717],{"class":52,"line":161},[50,718,358],{"class":60},[50,720,721],{"class":52,"line":167},[50,722,86],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":85},[50,724,725,727,729,731,734,737,739,741],{"class":52,"line":173},[50,726,57],{"class":56},[50,728,94],{"class":64},[50,730,97],{"class":56},[50,732,733],{"class":60}," document.",[50,735,736],{"class":100},"querySelector",[50,738,130],{"class":60},[50,740,195],{"class":133},[50,742,137],{"class":60},[50,744,745,747,750,752,755,758],{"class":52,"line":179},[50,746,57],{"class":56},[50,748,749],{"class":64}," root",[50,751,97],{"class":56},[50,753,754],{"class":60}," ReactDOM.",[50,756,757],{"class":100},"createRoot",[50,759,760],{"class":60},"(app);\n",[50,762,763,766,769,772,775],{"class":52,"line":184},[50,764,765],{"class":60},"root.",[50,767,768],{"class":100},"render",[50,770,771],{"class":60},"(\u003C",[50,773,774],{"class":645},"App",[50,776,777],{"class":60}," \u002F>);\n",[199,779,782],{"height":201,"style":202,"scrolling":203,"title":780,"src":781,"frameBorder":203,"loading":206,"allowTransparency":207,"allowFullScreen":207},"(66) React State Hook","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FabYMoKY?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FabYMoKY\">\n  (66) React State Hook\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"ht