ructuring — never mind object destructuring and all the rest.",[12,973,975],{"id":974},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,977,978],{},"This post is also published on my blog:",[216,980,981],{},[219,982,983],{},[222,984,987],{"href":985,"rel":986},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002F",[226],"It's Ray, not Array",[989,990,991],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}",{"title":46,"searchDepth":82,"depth":82,"links":993},[994,995,996,997,998],{"id":14,"depth":82,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":82,"text":23},{"id":252,"depth":82,"text":253},{"id":791,"depth":82,"text":792},{"id":974,"depth":82,"text":975},"React","2022-09-21 00:00:01","State is one of the most important things in React Hooks. How important? In short, the moment you need to change something that shows up on screen, you can't escape React state. In this post I'll walk through useState — starting from Vue's v-model so the Vue folks have something familiar to anchor to — then dig into how React handles data, why it's called one-way binding, and what types you can throw at useState.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics","5",{"title":6,"description":1001},false,"en\u002FReact\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics",[1011,1012,1013,38,1014,253,274],"You'll Learn React Eventually, So Why Not Now?","React Basics","Vue","re-render",null,"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F21\u002Freact-day-07-usestate-basics\u002F","2_eNi6tcSVJEHrh4EUe7gzddPoReObycjwelVhHrOoQ",{"newer":1019,"older":1023},{"url":1020,"title":1021,"date":1022},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F22\u002Freact-08-useeffect\u002F","React Basics: Getting to Know useEffect (and Side Effects) — (8)","2022-09-22 00:00:01",{"url":1024,"title":1025,"date":1026},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F09\u002F20\u002Fvue3-refs-dom-techniques\u002F","Different Ways to Grab DOM Elements with $refs in Vue 3","2022-09-20 10:33:59",[1028,1033,1038],{"url":1029,"title":1030,"date":1031,"readingMinutes":1032},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F14\u002Flearn-react-now-30-wrap-up-and-toc\u002F","Learn React Now — Wrap-up Notes & Full Table of Contents (30)","2022-10-14 00:00:01","4",{"url":1034,"title":1035,"date":1036,"readingMinutes":1037},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F13\u002Flearn-react-29-react-redux-quick-start\u002F","Learn React Eventually, So Why Not Now? - React Redux: Redux and a Quick Start - (29)","2022-10-13 00:00:01","6",{"url":1039,"title":1040,"date":1041,"readingMinutes":1032},"\u002Fen\u002Freact\u002F2022\u002F10\u002F12\u002Freact-day-28-router-lazy-loading\u002F","Why Learn React Eventually? Learn It Now! - React Router Lazy Loading (28)","2022-10-12 00:00:01",1784012786124]